001032_​interoperability_​apis_and_​encodings
Hanging paragraph in clause
<clause id="_interoperability_apis_and_encodings" obligation="normative">
<title>Interoperability: APIs and Encodings</title>
<p id="_416f6bda-0f44-e3f6-a209-a198f0078004">Interoperability and scalable fusion of spatial information across different data cubes is crucial and highly dependent on the use of robust international standards governing the access and transfer protocols for communication between client and server as well as among different servers [ <eref type="inline" bibitemid="Strobl_2017" citeas="Strobl 2017"/>].</p>

<p id="_a8daf678-6f12-c925-2b6a-9e0ef92f8203">For interoperability and federation, data cubes need to provide access and analytics using well-known and open interfaces. To serve the largest communities possible, Application Programming Interfaces (APIs) defined by open consensus standards are needed. The OGC Web Service standards have been implemented by most of the examples listed in <xref target="annex_b"/>. A Geospatial Coverage Data Cube Service may provide more than one interface.</p>
